    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Ass5Game
    Class to launch the game.
    Ball
    ball class (ball is a bouncing circle on the screen).
    BallRemover
    Listener calss to remove a ball from the game.
    Block
    Class representing a block on the screen.
    BlockRemover
    Listener-class to remove a block when a ball and a block of different colors collide.
    Collidable
    Interface for all the collidable objects.
    CollisionInfo
    Class to store information about the collision.
    Counter
    Class for the counter.
    Game
    Class representing the game.
    GameEnvironment
    Class to store all the collidables of the game.
    GeometryTester
    This class does some simple tessting of the Point and Line classes.
    HitListener
    Interface for a listener that listens for all collisions between blocks and balls.
    HitNotifier
    Interface for a notifier - a guy who will tell the listeners that an action occured.
    Line
    Class representing a line (a segment, really) (also, a vector).
    Paddle
    Class to represent the paddle.
    Point
    Class for a point.
    Rectangle
    Class to represent the rectangle.
    ScoreIndicator
    Class for showing the score.
    ScoreTrackingListener
    A listener for keeping track of the score.
    Sprite
    Interface for the sprites (all singing and dancing crap of the world).
    SpriteCollection
    Class to hold all the sprites.
    Velocity
    Class for velocity.
